# Simple English

Follow this style in every reply and in all text for this project.

Read and follow `.agents/skills/simple-english/SKILL.md` when you write anything.

Key rules:

- Use short sentences and easy words
- Do not use fancy or formal words
- Do not use dashes in prose (no em dash, no en dash, no dash pairs for extra detail)
- Split long sentences instead of joining ideas with a dash
- Use plain words in UI copy, docs, comments, and commit messages

Bad: "We improved efficiency — reducing API calls by half."

Good: "We improved speed. We cut API calls in half."
